Meh....color me suspicious.   First, there is no narrow-neck of land in Baja possible to cross in 1.5 days per Alma 22:32, and yet allowing the Nephites to be surrounded nearly on every side (vs. 29).  The entire peninsula is pretty much the same width without a distinguishable "narrow neck".   The peninsula needs more of a width-to-neck ratio similar to the land south of modern-day Panama City. Next, I'm not seeing a River Sidon in Baja. It would be south of the narrow-neck of land and have enough flow to float the bodies of dead Amlicites out to the sea (Alma 3:3).  
@32:15 The limitation going south is the Darien Gap, making Central America a peninsula of sorts.   @32:50 Nephites escaped into the south countries (Mormon 6:15) after the final battle, probably desperate enough to cross the Darien Gap.  
Great discussion though gents!  Fun to contemplate.

@bruceskousen5451
#1 DNA is still new science, especially when it comes to the study of ancient civilizations.  There is a lot of nuance, not least of which is the fact that the DNA you're referring to actually originates many thousands of years before The Book of Mormon (Ice Age genetics).
#2 I believe God's curse on the Lamanites was more than capable of changing their DNA. God can work such miracles if he chooses.
